==Abstract==

This IIP describes the version bits soft fork activation mechanism with support for height-based activation, combining elements from BIP 8 and BIP 9 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

Soft fork activation requires coordination between miners, nodes, and users. This mechanism provides:
* Miner signaling via version bits in block headers
* Support for both time-based (MTP) and height-based activation
* Configurable thresholds per deployment
* Safe activation with minimum activation height
* Clear failure state if threshold not reached

==Specification==

===Block Version Format===

<pre>
Bits 29-31: Version bits indicator (must be 001 = 0x20000000)
Bits 0-28:  Deployment signaling bits (1 = signal support)
</pre>

===Deployment States===

Each deployment progresses through a state machine:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! State !! Description
|-
| DEFINED || Deployment defined but not yet started
|-
| STARTED || Signaling period active
|-
| LOCKED_IN || Threshold reached, awaiting activation
|-
| ACTIVE || Rules enforced (terminal state)
|-
| FAILED || Timeout reached without threshold (terminal state)
|}

===State Transitions===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Current State !! Condition !! Next State
|-
| DEFINED || Start time/height not reached || DEFINED
|-
| DEFINED || Start time/height reached || STARTED
|-
| STARTED || Timeout reached || FAILED
|-
| STARTED || Threshold signals in period || LOCKED_IN
|-
| STARTED || Threshold not reached || STARTED
|-
| LOCKED_IN || Height < min_activation_height || LOCKED_IN
|-
| LOCKED_IN || Height >= min_activation_height || ACTIVE
|}

===Deployment Parameters===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Parameter !! Type !! Description
|-
| bit || int (0-28) || Version bit for signaling
|-
| nStartTime || int64 || Start of signaling (timestamp or height)
|-
| nTimeout || int64 || Timeout/failure deadline
|-
| min_activation_height || int32 || Minimum height before ACTIVE
|-
| use_height_based_activation || bool || Use height instead of MTP
|-
| threshold || int || Required signals (default: 90% of period)
|-
| period || int || Blocks per signaling period (default: 2016)
|}

===Special Values===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Constant !! Value !! Meaning
|-
| ALWAYS_ACTIVE || -1 || Deployment is always active
|-
| NEVER_ACTIVE || -2 || Deployment is permanently disabled
|-
| NO_TIMEOUT || INT64_MAX || No timeout
|}

===INTcoin Adaptations===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Aspect !! BIP 9 !! IIP-37
|-
| Default threshold || 95% || 90%
|-
| Activation timing || MTP only || MTP or height
|-
| Period || Fixed 2016 || Configurable
|-
| Threshold || Fixed 1916/2016 || Configurable
|}

IIP-37 intentionally does '''not''' support mandatory lock-in at timeout (BIP 8 LOT=true). If threshold is not reached, the deployment fails.

